- Choose either Criterion or Unity as the testing framework and add a make test target to the build system. - DONE
- Write an initial TDD(Test-Driven Development) set for vector and line.

```
typedef struct {
    Vec_Line  lines;
    size_t    cur_row;
    size_t    cur_col;
    size_t    scroll_row;
} EditorBuffer;

void eb_init(EditorBuffer *eb);
void eb_insert(EditorBuffer *eb, int ch);
void eb_backspace(EditorBuffer *eb);
void eb_newline(EditorBuffer *eb);

void handle_key(EditorBuffer *eb){
    if(IsKeyPressed(KEY_ENTER))      eb_newline(eb);
    else if(IsKeyPressed(KEY_BACKSPACE)) eb_backspace(eb);
    else if(IsKeyPressed(KEY_LEFT))  eb_move_left(eb);
    // ...
    int ch; while((ch = GetCharPressed())) eb_insert(eb, ch);
}

```
- As implement new Editorbuffer API, white corresponding unit tests.
- (Optional): Set up CI with Github Actions - copy a template and configure it to run gcc -fsantize=adress &&make test.